  "text": "Then, the stability of the RhB conjugation was performed by measuring the dye release in the same conditions (Figure 2A ). After 24 h of incubation, the released RhB was below 15% in all cases, suggesting the system reliability for in vitro and in vivo NPs tracking. Additionally, as reported in Figure 2B , the fluorescence intensity of PLGA-PEG-RhB-NPs was not greatly affected by the incubation media showing that, once conjugated, the dye abolishes its pH-dependent emission properties [CITATION_1] . ",
